numInterfaces.name: numInterfaces
numInterfaces.description: The number of Adaptec network interfaces present on this system.

numPorts.name: numPorts
numPorts.description: The number of Adaptec network ports present on this system.

numCards.name: numCards
numCards.description: The number of Adaptec network adapters present on this system.

interfaceStatsTable.name: interfaceStatsTable
interfaceStatsTable.description: The table listing Adaptec network interface statistics.

interfaceStatsEntry.name: interfaceStatsEntry
interfaceStatsEntry.description: Each entry lists statistics for a single network interface.

iInterfaceIndex.name: iInterfaceIndex
iInterfaceIndex.description: A unique value assigned to each interface This is an increasing numeric value ranging between 1 and the value of NumInterfaces.

iInterfaceName.name: iInterfaceName
iInterfaceName.description: The descriptive name assigned to the interface at the time the interface was configured.

iInterfacePorts.name: iInterfacePorts
iInterfacePorts.description: The number of ports in the interface. An interface may consist of one or more ports.

iPermNetAddress.name: iPermNetAddress
iPermNetAddress.description: The permanent network address assigned to this interface. This is the node address stored permanently in the adapter.

iCurrentNetAddress.name: iCurrentNetAddress
iCurrentNetAddress.description: The network address currently assigned this interface. This address may be administered by software.

iDataRate.name: iDataRate
iDataRate.description: This is the rate at which data is transferred over this interface, measured in MPBS.

iTotalPacketsTransmitted.name: iTotalPacketsTransmitted
iTotalPacketsTransmitted.description: This is the total number of packets transmitted over this interface.

iTotalBytesTransmitted.name: iTotalBytesTransmitted
iTotalBytesTransmitted.description: This is the total number of bytes transmitted over this interface.

iTotalPacketsReceived.name: iTotalPacketsReceived
iTotalPacketsReceived.description: This is the total number of packets received over this interface.

iTotalBytesReceived.name: iTotalBytesReceived
iTotalBytesReceived.description: This is the total number of bytes received over this interface.

iTotalTransmitErrors.name: iTotalTransmitErrors
iTotalTransmitErrors.description: This is the total number of Transmit errors seen on this interface.

iTotalReceiveErrors.name: iTotalReceiveErrors
iTotalReceiveErrors.description: This is the total number of Receive errors seen on this interface.

iInterfaceType.name: iInterfaceType
iInterfaceType.description: This is the interface type. standalone indicates a single port configuration. failover indicates a two port group supporting failover resiliency. loadBalanced indicates a multiple port group providing load balancing.

portStatsTable.name: portStatsTable
portStatsTable.description: The table listing Adaptec network port statistics.

portStatsEntry.name: portStatsEntry
portStatsEntry.description: Each entry lists statistics for a single network port.

pInterfaceIndex.name: pInterfaceIndex
pInterfaceIndex.description: A unique value assigned to each interface This is an increasing numeric value ranging between 1 and the value of NumInterfaces.

pPortIndex.name: pPortIndex
pPortIndex.description: A unique value assigned to each port on a particular interface. This is an increasing numeric value ranging between 1 and the value of iInterfacePorts for the interface indexed by iInterfaceIndex.

pPortName.name: pPortName
pPortName.description: The descriptive name assigned to the port. This may not be supported by all operating systems.

pCardNumber.name: pCardNumber
pCardNumber.description: The value of cpCardIndex that corresponds to this port.

pCardPortNumber.name: pCardPortNumber
pCardPortNumber.description: The value of cpPortIndex that corresponds to this port.

pPermNetAddress.name: pPermNetAddress
pPermNetAddress.description: The permanent network address assigned to this port. This is the node address stored permanently in the adapter.

pCurrentNetAddress.name: pCurrentNetAddress
pCurrentNetAddress.description: The network address currently assigned to this port. This address may be administered by software.

pDataRate.name: pDataRate
pDataRate.description: This is the rate at which data is transferred over this port, measured in MPBS.

pTotalPacketsTransmitted.name: pTotalPacketsTransmitted
pTotalPacketsTransmitted.description: This is the total number of packets transmitted over this port.

pTotalBytesTransmitted.name: pTotalBytesTransmitted
pTotalBytesTransmitted.description: This is the total number of bytes transmitted over this port.

pTotalPacketsReceived.name: pTotalPacketsReceived
pTotalPacketsReceived.description: This is the total number of packets received over this port.

pTotalBytesReceived.name: pTotalBytesReceived
pTotalBytesReceived.description: This is the total number of bytes received over this port.

pTotalTransmitErrors.name: pTotalTransmitErrors
pTotalTransmitErrors.description: This is the total number of transmit errors seen on this port.

pTotalReceiveErrors.name: pTotalReceiveErrors
pTotalReceiveErrors.description: This is the total number of receive errors seen on this port.

pStatus.name: pStatus
pStatus.description: The current status of the port. portActive indicates a functioning port. portDown indicates a port that is not functioning. portDisabled indicates a port that has been down for some time or has demonstrated a serious problem which should be addressed by the system administrator. portInStandby indicates a port which is designated as a backup in a failover interface.

cardInformationTable.name: cardInformationTable
cardInformationTable.description: A table listing Adaptec network card information.

cardInformationEntry.name: cardInformationEntry
cardInformationEntry.description: Each entry lists information about a single network card.

cCardIndex.name: cCardIndex
cCardIndex.description: A unique value assigned to each network card. This is an increasing numeric value ranging between 1 and the value of NumCards.

cCardDescription.name: cCardDescription
cCardDescription.description: The descriptive name assigned to the network card.

cPortsOnCard.name: cPortsOnCard
cPortsOnCard.description: The number of ports on the network card.

cardPortInfoTable.name: cardPortInfoTable
cardPortInfoTable.description: This table indicates the interface and port number associated with each port on all installed network cards.

cardPortInfoEntry.name: cardPortInfoEntry
cardPortInfoEntry.description: Each entry lists information for a single port on a network card.

cpCardIndex.name: cpCardIndex
cpCardIndex.description: A unique value assigned to each network card. This is an increasing numeric value ranging between 1 and the value of NumCards.

cpPortIndex.name: cpPortIndex
cpPortIndex.description: A unique value assigned to each port on a particular network card. This is an increasing numeric value ranging between 1 and the value of cPortsOnCard for the card indexed by cCardIndex.

cpInterfaceNumber.name: cpInterfaceNumber
cpInterfaceNumber.description: The value of pInterfaceIndex that corresponds to this port. If this port is not part of an interface it will be set to 0

cpPortNumber.name: cpPortNumber
cpPortNumber.description: The value of pPortIndex that corresponds to this port. If this port is not part of an interface it will be set to 0

cpTableNumber1.name: cpTableNumber1
cpTableNumber1.description: The value of Lan Adapter component table rows that correspond to this port. This provides a mapping to entries in an SNMP implementation of the Desktop Management Interface Lan Adapter Component. If this port is not in use on the system this value will be set to 0
